FHQ Backend (c++ version)

Used sources from https://github.com/nikhilm/qhttpserver

Step 1.
Need to install:
# apt-get install libqt5sql5-mysql

make fhqbackend
$ qmake && make

Step 2.
If you already has database and you has correct config please skip this step.
# apt-get install mysql-server

create config:
$ sudo ./fhqbackend --example-config > /etc/fhq/backend/config.ini

create database:
$ ./fhqbackend --create-database

Step 3.
update database:
$ ./fhqbackend  --update-database

Step 4.
run server:
$ ./fhqbackend --server

Step 5.
check you server:
http://localhost:8010/





